    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by the elite tier matchups of **Yordan Alvarez** (77.33) and **Carson Benge** (67.06). **Yordan Alvarez** serves as our premier play against Pallante, whose 4.44 xERA provides a soft landing for a hitter of his caliber, buoyed further by a solid order position. Simultaneously, **Carson Benge** benefits from a strong platoon advantage against Taillon, while **Colt Keith** (66.56) overcomes a wind-in factor thanks to a prime #3 spot and a favorable matchup against Bello. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a high-upside start; while his #8 spot hurts, his 92% stolen base success rate against the specific cadence of Peralta earns him a massive boost in our scarcity-weighted 5x5 framework.\n\nThe primary conflict in today\u2019s optimization centered on the fringe utility slot. **Junior Caminero** (53.51) ultimately edged out the lower-scoring cohort because, despite facing an elite arm in Skenes, his dynamic platoon splits and premium #2 lineup spot offered a higher floor than **Gary Sanchez** (52.55) or **Kazuma Okamoto** (53.16). While **Caleb Durbin** (40.36) remains active, he sits precariously close to the bench floor; facing Skubal with wind blowing in makes him a strictly volume-based play for his stolen base utility, as his raw scoring potential is severely hampered by the SP\u2019s elite skill profile. We continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Victor Scott II**, whose absence from the active lineup\u2014or the major league roster in the case of **Zac Veen**\u2014continues to compress our available options for the MI/OF depth roles held by reserves like **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Josh Smith**, and **Luis Pena**. Managers should keep a close watch on weather reports, as the wind-in warnings for **Colt Keith** and **Caleb Durbin** represent the highest variance points in today's projection.",
